    "description": "CDX.NA.IG.46 CDS index option (CDSO) volatility surface calibrated from a 3×3 (expiry × strike) grid of lognormal spread-vol quotes against the index hazard curve in initial_market. Demonstrates how analysts build a credit-derivative vol surface alongside the underlying credit curve. The vol_surface step uses OptionVol quotes where underlying='CDX-NA-IG-46' and strikes are CDS spread levels in decimal (e.g., 0.0040 = 40bp). The SABR model is calibrated per-expiry with β=1.0 (lognormal) and spot_override = 0.00552848 (~55.28 bp), matching the 5y par spread implied by the initial_market hazard curve (λ ≈ 92bp × (1−R) ≈ 55 bp). The produced VolSurface is keyed as 'CDX-NA-IG-46-CDSO-VOL' and is retrievable via MarketContext::get_surface(). Note: settings.fail_on_bad_fit is set to false because the input grid is flat in the strike dimension; SABR (β=1) cannot pin a near-flat smile to engine tolerance (1e-12) when ν is bounded away from zero. The produced surface is queryable but does not pin to the input quotes at solver tolerance — replace with a non-flat smile (e.g., +/- 50bps of vol on the 40 / 75 bp wings) to exercise SABR with strict fit. Used as a prerequisite for 12 (full credit desk composite).",
